					</div>
				</div>
			</slide>
			<slide id="usage">
				<title>API Value = Potential × Usage</title>
				<ul>
					<li><em>Designed</em> as digital building blocks focusing on value</li>
					<li><em>Published</em> easily thereby evolving to the platform</li>
					<li><em>Discovered</em> in a catalog of all digital building blocks</li>
					<li><em>Subscribed</em> so that the building block can be used</li>
					<li><em>Used</em> to build new products</li>
					<li><em>Improved</em> to make the digital building block more valuable</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="openness">
				<title>Openness and Automation</title>
				<img src="open-api-openapi.png" title="Open API ≠ OpenAPI" style="float: right ; width : 20% ; margin : 0% 5% 5% 5% ; "/>
				<ul>
					<li>Create an <em>open API platform</em> that itself is open as well</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Open API</em> platform means any API can be added to it</li>
						<li>Open <em>API platform</em> means the platform is built openly</li>
					</ul>
					<li><em>Communicating value through the platform</em> needs open formats</li>
					<li><em>API value</em> needs to be communicated through the toolchain</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="value-chain">
				<title>API Value Chain</title>
				<img src="API-value-chain.png" class="fullsize"/>
			</slide>
			<slide id="representation">
				<title>Out-of-line or Inline?</title>
				<ul>
					<li><em>OpenAPI</em> has become a popular choice for API toolchains</li>
					<ul>
						<li>It is technical in nature but has built-in extension capabilities</li>
					</ul>
					<li>Out-of-line provides better decoupling from specific formats</li>
					<li>Inline allows easier flow through toolchains and ecosystems</li>
					<li>Combining both combines both advantages</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Media types</em> allow standalone representation and exchange</li>
						<li><em>Extensions</em> allow representation to be embedded into existing toolchains</li>
					</ul>
				</ul>
			</slide>
		</part>
